# Fix for the STM32F4 RTC crash on date/time register changes.
#
# The original STM32F4_RTC model applied time/date register writes field-by-field,
# which could produce a transiently invalid DateTime (e.g. day-of-month 0 when
# setting a day divisible by 10), throwing ArgumentOutOfRangeException.
#
# STM32F4_RTC_Fixed applies the write atomically and corrects the
# write-protection / init-mode guard, so the previously failing reproduction passes.

using sysbus

# Load the fixed RTC model implementation at runtime. $ORIGIN expands to the
# directory of this script, so the files resolve regardless of the working
# directory (e.g. under renode-test in CI).
include $ORIGIN/STM32F4_RTC_Fixed.cs

mach create "stm32f4"
machine LoadPlatformDescription $ORIGIN/stm32f4_fix.repl
